00:17:34.020 --> 00:17:35.380
So even when I work on projects,

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:36.920
I don't necessarily enable all of the rules.

00:17:37.010 --> 00:17:38.780
I typically enable like a couple subsets.

00:17:38.920 --> 00:17:40.740
So I just think sometimes it can be intimidating

00:17:40.790 --> 00:17:43.180
to imagine 800 rules being applied over your code phase.

00:17:43.740 --> 00:17:45.740
So, you know, the default rule set is pretty small.

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:47.800
It's covers things like unused imports,

00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:50.340
you know, things that are pretty common

00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:51.700
and relatively unobjectionable.

00:17:52.480 --> 00:17:53.860
And then we have all these different categories

00:17:54.200 --> 00:17:56.240
for ways that you kind of level up the level of coverage.

00:17:57.320 --> 00:17:57.680
Yeah.

00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:02.460
I'd take pretty much the defaults as well on all my projects,

00:18:02.860 --> 00:18:07.900
