00:19:56.890 --> 00:19:59.260
Well, first of all, of course, there's building a type checker,

00:19:59.520 --> 00:20:03.720
but there's also building what I would call a type-aware linter.

00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:07.460
You could imagine that rough itself could actually get a lot more powerful

00:20:07.610 --> 00:20:09.360
if it could do all sorts of type inference.

00:20:10.080 --> 00:20:12.800
We have some rules that are only supposed to activate on dictionaries,

