a couple of things like that and one to compile the changes.

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:45.360
And, you know, you look up, for me, I look up the docs.

00:31:45.580 --> 00:31:47.980
I go, okay, well, here's how I'm going to shorten that

00:31:48.050 --> 00:31:49.440
to something I never think about again.

00:31:50.190 --> 00:31:50.880
So it doesn't matter.

00:31:51.040 --> 00:31:52.120
That's totally fine, right?

00:31:52.360 --> 00:31:53.000
That's totally fine.

00:31:54.440 --> 00:31:58.140
But you do got to consider, I guess, the workflow for new people.

00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:01.400
Maybe that's a good place to talk about the features here.

00:32:02.440 --> 00:32:04.220
So one of the things that really...

00:32:04.260 --> 00:32:05.380
There's a lot here.

00:32:05.460 --> 00:32:07.660
One of the things that, even though it's number three

00:32:07.850 --> 00:32:13.560
on the list of four things, is the Python command.

00:32:13.780 --> 00:32:19.100
So uv Python install, uv Python list, all of those kinds of things.

00:32:20.380 --> 00:32:25.540
I mean, maybe we should start there because without that, we don't have any Python.

